{
  "texts": [
    "However, identifying such inputs is often complex, especially for legacy code.",
    "Users typically rely on functional testing inputs, which may not produce the highest execution times, leading to underestimation of the WCET.",
    "Another challenge is in measurement collection.",
    "Accurate measurement of execution time is crucial.",
    "Performance Monitoring Counters (PMCs) [84] are often used for this purpose, but their inherent latency and the potential for intrusive modifications to the system can introduce inaccuracies."
  ]
}